         <div>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">Shenzi said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">“Be humble and restrained to establish yourself, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">be hard and strong to establish your intent, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">be loyal and truthful to revert to devotion, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">welcome your friends to establish the way, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">refine the law to yield ability. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] , </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">conducting rituals with humility, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">the way will not be partial; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">conducting talks with trust, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">words will not be partial, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">continuing the intent with strength[...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] If it obtains usage in the world, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">if it is equally distributed and broadly implemented, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">one can rely on virtue and approach righteousness. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">The people’s [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] objects to provide for the body, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">to stay in the middle and not be partial, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">to use virtue to [...], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">therefore it is said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">[?] [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">Emoluments do not hamper his will, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">therefore he is said strong. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">He wears a bamboo hat on his head, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">holds the bamboo basket and holds the hoe, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0065_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">when in the ditches in the fields he uses the plow necessarily [...] </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
